Suppose an MBA graduate interested in international relations is studying a model of economic interactions between two countries: Country A and Country B. The model is based on the concept of Game Theory, represented by a 2x2 payoff matrix as follows:

\[
\begin{{array}}{{cc}}
\begin{{array}}{{c|c}}
\multicolumn{2}{{c}}{{\text{{Country B}}}} \\
\cline{2-2}
& \begin{{array}}{{cc}} \text{{Cooperate}} & \text{{Defect}} \end{{array}} \\
\end{{array}} \\
\hline
\begin{{array}}{{c|c}}
\text{{Cooperate}} & (3,3) & (0,5) \\
\hline
\text{{Defect}} & (5,0) & (1,1) \\
\end{{array}}
\end{{array}}
\]

The numbers in the cells represent the payoffs to Country A and Country B respectively. This graduate wants to calculate the Nash Equilibrium of this game.

1. Find the Nash Equilibrium of this game.
2. Prove that the Nash Equilibrium you found is indeed a Nash Equilibrium.
